Nested Loops:  a loop insdie the another loop
Nested loops are loops placed inside other loops.
 They are a common programming concept used to handle repetitive tasks within repetitive tasks. Each time the outer loop runs once, the inner loop runs through all of its iterations.
An inner loop within the repetative block of outer loop

for(let i=1; i<=3;i++){
  document.write(i,"<br>");
  for(let j=1; j<=4;j++){
    document.write(j," ");
  }
  document.write("<br>");
} 
ïƒ¨inner loop execute 1 time and outer loop excutes completely
